---
title: Middle Eastern Sausage Meatball Stew with Bulgur Wheat
description: This speedy sausage meatball stew is a hearty and comforting dish that can be ready from pan to plate in just 35 minutes, perfect when you don’t feel like spending all night in the kitchen! Seasoned with Middle Eastern spices for a sweet and fragrant aroma, this dish will fill your kitchen with delicious and enticing smells.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/middle-eastern-sausage-meatball-stew-c9bd2227-27708461.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/middle-eastern-sausage-meatball-stew-5da7552d49913a232038a1a0-28f63bf4.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/middle-eastern-sausage-meatball-stew-5da7552d49913a232038a1a0
author: Mimi Morley
time required: 35 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 741 kcal
  fat: 31 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 80 g
  sugar: 18 g
  protein: 38 g
  sodium: 5 g
  serving size: 682
servings: 2
course: main course
cuisine: Middle Eastern
---

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Halve the
@yellow pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm chunks. Peel and
grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Put the @pork sausage meat{225%g} into a #bowl{} and add the @ground cumin{2%tsp}
and @panko breadcrumbs{10%g}. Mix with your hands until well combined, then shape
into 4-5 walnut sized meatballs per person. Pop them on a #plate{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Pour the @water for the bulgur{240%ml} into a #saucepan{} and bring to the boil.
Stir in the @bulgur wheat{120%g} and half the @chicken stock powder{2%tsp}. Bring
back up to the boil, simmer for ~{1%minute}, pop a #lid{} on the pan and remove
from the heat. Leave to the side for ~{12-15%minutes} or until ready to serve.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once the
oil is hot, add the pepper and cook until the pepper is charred, ~{3-4%minutes}.
Stir only twice in this time as you want the pepper to get some nice colour. Once
charred, remove the pepper to a bowl. Pop your pan back on medium-high heat with
a drizzle of oil if the pan is dry.

Add the meatballs to the frying pan, fry until evenly browned on the outside,
~{3-4%minutes}, turning occasionally. Move the meatballs to the edge of the pan
and add the onion along with a pinch of @salt{pinch}, @pepper{pinch} and
@sugar{pinch}. Fry with the meatballs until softened, ~{5%minutes} stirring
frequently. Add the pepper back into the pan along with the garlic and
@chermoula spice mix{1}. Stir and cook for ~{1%minute}, pour in the
@tomato passata{1%200g jar} and @water{}.

Stir in the remaining chicken stock powder, then add a pinch of salt, pepper and
sugar and simmer the stew until nicely thickened, ~{5-7%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The meatballs are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, stir through the @baby spinach{125%g}(fresh) a handful at a time until
wilted.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if the stew looks a little dry. Taste the stew and
> add salt and pepper if necessary.

Fluff up the bulgur wheat with a #fork{} and stir through a drizzle of
@olive oil{drizzle}. Spoon into #bowls{} and top with the stew. Finish with a
spoonful of @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g} and enjoy!